The paper deals with designing convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for medical image classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on visualization techniques to understand the decision-making process of the model, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of communicating the model decision process well, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
